DEM_MASK_POLY: A polygon feature used to mask the input DEM.
DEM_MASKED: The input DEM masked using an input polygon feature.
PITFILL: The input DEM with the TauDEM Pit Remove algorithm applied to it.
DINFFLOWDIR_ANG: Flow direction raster produced by applying the TauDEM D-infity Flow Directions algorithm to the pit filled DEM.
RASTERIZED_CHANNEL: The input channel polygon or line network converted to a raster where the channel cells have the value 1 and all other cells have the value 0.
DINFFLOWDIR_SLP: Slope raster produced by applying the TauDEM D-infinity Flow Directions algorithm to the pit filled DEM.
AREADINF_SCA: A raster of specific catchment area produced by applying that TauDEM algorithm to the D-infinity flow direction raster.
HAND_RASTER: A raster where each pixel value is the height above the nearest drainage area, produced using the D-infinity Distance Down TauDEM algorithm.
TWI_RASTER: A raster of Topographic Wetness Index produced using TauDEMs application of the algorithm.
